<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title><![CDATA[Blog by Joshua Jones]]></title><description><![CDATA[Personal site of Joshua Jones a Mechanical Engineer building Software Engineering skills in 2020.]]></description><link>https://jonesprojects.co.uk</link><generator>GatsbyJS</generator><lastBuildDate>Thu, 02 Jul 2020 12:17:02 GMT</lastBuildDate><item><title><![CDATA[Using git locally]]></title><description><![CDATA[Here's a short post on using git locally]]></description><link>https://jonesprojects.co.uk/posts/how to set up a local repo</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://jonesprojects.co.uk/posts/how to set up a local repo</guid><pubDate>Sun, 02 Feb 2020 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;h1 id=&quot;using-git-locally&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#using-git-locally&quot; aria-label=&quot;using git locally permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Using Git locally&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ever wanted to use git version control without using github, and running it on your own computer?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is a collection of commands to get started with a locally hosted repo that you can use for local development without having to upload to any server. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Obviously you’re not safe from hardware failure and you are missing lot’s of github specific features including collaboration (a biggie!), but being closer to the terminal and a self-hosted git solution can be fun for working on toy projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A git workflow for using a local file store as your master&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;why-use-git-locally&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#why-use-git-locally&quot; aria-label=&quot;why use git locally permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Why use git locally?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It works completely offline and can be used to practice git commands and local development practices, without polluting your github account with loads of tiny repo’s with unpolished work in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Think of it like a personal sandbox for you to make unlimited private repo’s to practice development and development with git. It’s just your computer + git.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Less mental overhead than managing a github account + repo’s if you’re only making toy projects for learning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I’m using git locally with two directories:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A directory called &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;/Code&lt;/code&gt; which has projects in.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A directory called &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;/CodeBackups&lt;/code&gt; which has bare git repo’s of the projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;basic-set-up&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#basic-set-up&quot; aria-label=&quot;basic set up permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Basic set up&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;making-your-backup-location&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#making-your-backup-location&quot; aria-label=&quot;making your backup location permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Making your backup location&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;mkdir CodeBackups&lt;/code&gt; or whatever you want to call it to make a new folder&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make a new a project directory &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;CodeBackups/projectName&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;cd into the project in the &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;CodeBackups&lt;/code&gt; directory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;run the command &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;git init --bare&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This creates a github-like repo with no checked-out branches, this way you can push to any branch in the repo including master.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;development&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#development&quot; aria-label=&quot;development permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Development&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In your existing codebase in somewhere like &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;code/projectname run&lt;/code&gt;git init` to make a new repo&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;use git remote add origin &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;~/CodeBackups/projectName&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;add and commit your changes then run &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;git push&lt;/code&gt; to push your code to the &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;codeBackups/projectName&lt;/code&gt; repo.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can now do stuff like delete your working directory and clone from the CodeBackups repo to carry on working at any time, and use git how you would normally sue it, but with a local repo.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;what-was-the-point-of-this-again&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#what-was-the-point-of-this-again&quot; aria-label=&quot;what was the point of this again permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;What was the point of this again?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Running your own local git repo shows you what is happening behind the scenes, a repo made with  &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;git init --bare&lt;/code&gt; is what each of your github repo’s are, and is how people did stuff before github.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most (new)developers only ever use github and never use git on it’s own so at least for me I always wanted to understand the mental models of git before hooking into github.&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[Hello 2020!]]></title><description><![CDATA[2020 is the year of embracing code and becoming a software engineer!]]></description><link>https://jonesprojects.co.uk/posts/2020 is the year of embracing code</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://jonesprojects.co.uk/posts/2020 is the year of embracing code</guid><pubDate>Mon, 06 Jan 2020 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;h1 id=&quot;2020-is-the-year-of-embracing-code&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#2020-is-the-year-of-embracing-code&quot; aria-label=&quot;2020 is the year of embracing code permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;2020 is the year of embracing code.&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My first work experience in high school was learning some Java interning over the summer at a small software company. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I learned a lot but decided code wasn’t for me.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I felt much more at home making physical stuff so I went to study mechanical engineering instead. I learned, I built things, and I got a masters degree along the way. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Code did keep pulling me back every now and then, while interning for cummins turbo technologies I wrote data analysis scripts in Python as one of the few people in my department who could to predict how damaged they get in use.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After my masters degree I went into programme (project) management at Aston Martin launching new models. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I spent 2 years at Aston Martin and during that time I started taking tutorials on &lt;a href=&quot;http://freecodecamp.com&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener noreferrer&quot;&gt;freecodecamp.com&lt;/a&gt; to learn fullstack javascript development as a hobby.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I found a &lt;a href=&quot;https://news.ycombinator.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener noreferrer&quot;&gt;https://news.ycombinator.com/&lt;/a&gt; “who’s hiring?” thread for a programming job, completed a few take home tests and some team-fit calls and now I work for an American start up company that is fully remote! &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Since September I’ve been writing Javascript everyday at home!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;what-im-learning-in-january&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#what-im-learning-in-january&quot; aria-label=&quot;what im learning in january permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;What I’m learning in January&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ReactJS  - which incidentally is how this blog is made.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Redux&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Typescript&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Redux.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Typescript.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Css / Sass.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;I can use css frameworks like bootstrap, bulma, and tailwindCSS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;I am also able to write python for engineering and web applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;what-im-reading-in-january&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#what-im-reading-in-january&quot; aria-label=&quot;what im reading in january permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;What I’m reading in January&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;i-finished-reading-the-checklist-manifesto-by-atul-gawande&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#i-finished-reading-the-checklist-manifesto-by-atul-gawande&quot; aria-label=&quot;i finished reading the checklist manifesto by atul gawande permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;I finished reading The Checklist Manifesto by Atul Gawande&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This book is all about how to get things right in a world where our work is increasingly complex.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It follows the path of Atul, a leading surgeon, on his study of checklists used by pilots and other professions and how their use in operating theaters around the world dramatically lowered surgery complications and deaths.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Atul gives us an entertaining story but also the introspection on how checklists can help anyones job become less error prone and improve the quality and safety checks in whatever we might happen to be doing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Checklist_Manifesto&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener noreferrer&quot;&gt;Link to the book on wiki&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[How I built this site with GatsbyJS]]></title><description><![CDATA[A Super simple guide to building a blog with gatsby and using github-pages to host]]></description><link>https://jonesprojects.co.uk/posts/How to build this site with GatsbyJS</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://jonesprojects.co.uk/posts/How to build this site with GatsbyJS</guid><pubDate>Mon, 06 Jan 2020 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;h2 id=&quot;a-super-simple-guide-to-building-a-blog-with-gatsby-and-using-github-pages-to-host&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#a-super-simple-guide-to-building-a-blog-with-gatsby-and-using-github-pages-to-host&quot; aria-label=&quot;a super simple guide to building a blog with gatsby and using github pages to host permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;A Super simple guide to building a blog with gatsby and using github-pages to host:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This article is mainly my personal notes for GatsbyJS and the lumen starter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;what-is-gatsbyjs&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#what-is-gatsbyjs&quot; aria-label=&quot;what is gatsbyjs permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;What is GatsbyJS?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gatsbyjs.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener noreferrer&quot;&gt;A static site generator for ReactJS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;what-is-lumen&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#what-is-lumen&quot; aria-label=&quot;what is lumen permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;What is Lumen?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A minimal, lightweight and mobile-first starter for creating blogs using Gatsby. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;getting-set-up&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#getting-set-up&quot; aria-label=&quot;getting set up permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Getting set up&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install node &lt;a href=&quot;https://nodejs.org/en/download/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener noreferrer&quot;&gt;https://nodejs.org/en/download/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Install gatsby&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;gatsby-highlight&quot; data-language=&quot;sh&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;language-sh&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-sh&quot;&gt;npm install -g gatsby-cli&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;create-a-gatsby-site&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#create-a-gatsby-site&quot; aria-label=&quot;create a gatsby site permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Create a Gatsby site&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use the Gatsby CLI to create a new site, specifying the Lumen starter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;gatsby-highlight&quot; data-language=&quot;sh&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;language-sh&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-sh&quot;&gt;gatsby new blog https://github.com/alxshelepenok/gatsby-starter-lumen&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;start-developing&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#start-developing&quot; aria-label=&quot;start developing permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Start Developing&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Navigate into your new site’s directory and start it up.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;gatsby-highlight&quot; data-language=&quot;sh&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;language-sh&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-sh&quot;&gt;cd blog
gatsby develop&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;open-the-source-code-and-start-editing&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#open-the-source-code-and-start-editing&quot; aria-label=&quot;open the source code and start editing permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Open the source code and start editing!&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your site is now running at &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8000&lt;/code&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;how-to-actually-edit-stuff-the-simple-way&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#how-to-actually-edit-stuff-the-simple-way&quot; aria-label=&quot;how to actually edit stuff the simple way permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;How to actually edit stuff the simple way&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are a bunch of files and folders in the /blog/ folder that are needed to build the site, to actually edit the blog to your own content there are a small number of folders and files you actually have to edit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;important-files-and-folders&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#important-files-and-folders&quot; aria-label=&quot;important files and folders permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Important files and folders&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;/content/pages holds the about and contact pages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;/Content/posts holds the blog posts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;/config.js holds the meta data for the site and social media accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;/static/photo.jpg holds the picture for the user pic and the favicon&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;/static/media holds pictures and other media assets for blog posts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;developing&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#developing&quot; aria-label=&quot;developing permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Developing&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can make edits to blog posts &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;(.md)&lt;/code&gt; files and save and the localhost:8000 page in your browser will auto-load your changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To see edits to config.js you need to stop the &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;gatsby develop&lt;/code&gt; command (usually ctrl+c in your terminal) and run it again.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;publishing-to-github-pages&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#publishing-to-github-pages&quot; aria-label=&quot;publishing to github pages permalink&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Publishing to github pages&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;npm run deploy &amp;#x3C; - this builds the site to the &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;/public&lt;/code&gt; folder this is the folder to upload to github pages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;move the contents of public to your gh-pages repository and the site will build from there in a few minutes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</content:encoded></item></channel></rss>